[36m@@ -0,0 +1,161 @@[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m[32mname: install-check[m
[32m+[m[32mdescription: Check, fix, or extend requirements/install.sh and its docker/Dockerfile coverage when adding a new embodied model or environment in RLinf, so the install logic reuses common utilities, keeps system deps in sys_deps.sh, pins/forks git deps, avoids ad-hoc pyproject/core-dep hacks, and every new model/env gets a matching Dockerfile build stage. Use when writing or cleaning up an install_<model>_model / install_<env>_env function, fixing a flaky or non-portable install path, or reviewing an install.sh / Dockerfile diff for convention compliance.[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Install check: install.sh + Dockerfile conventions for a new model/env[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m`requirements/install.sh` installs every embodied model + env combo, and[m
[32m+[m[32m`docker/Dockerfile` builds an image per target. New contributions tend to[m
[32m+[m[32mcopy-paste an existing block and hack it until it works on one machine —[m
[32m+[m[32mre-cloning repos by hand, `apt-get`-ing a package, pinning `ray`, `sed`-ing[m
[32m+[m[32m`pyproject.toml`, and forgetting the Dockerfile entirely. This skill is the[m
[32m+[m[32mconvention checklist plus a linter that flags those anti-patterns.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> Sibling skill: [add-install-docker-ci-e2e](../add-install-docker-ci-e2e/SKILL.md)[m
[32m+[m[32m> *wires up* a new model/env (register, Dockerfile stage, CI jobs). This skill[m
[32m+[m[32m> checks the *quality* of the install function and that the Dockerfile keeps up.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAll paths below are relative to the repo root.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Run the check (start here)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe harness is [check.sh](check.sh). Run it before and after editing[m
[32m+[m[32m`requirements/install.sh` or `docker/Dockerfile`:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mbash .claude/skills/install-check/check.sh[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIt scans the install script for each convention, then verifies every model in[m
[32m+[m[32m`SUPPORTED_MODELS` and env in `SUPPORTED_ENVS` has a matching `--model` /[m
[32m+[m[32m`--env` install invocation in `docker/Dockerfile`. It prints line numbers + fix[m
[32m+[m[32mhints and exits non-zero if anything is flagged. Paths can be passed explicitly:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mbash .claude/skills/install-check/check.sh requirements/install.sh docker/Dockerfile[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHeuristics **over-report** — every hit is a line to *review*, not an automatic[m
[32m+[m[32mbug. Some are legitimate exceptions (see Gotchas). The goal when fixing is: each[m
[32m+[m[32mflagged item is either resolved or consciously kept with a one-line reason.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## The conventions[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Reuse common utilities — don't rebuild them.** Clone with[m
[32m+[m[32m   `clone_or_reuse_repo`, install flash-attn with `install_flash_attn`, apex[m
[32m+[m[32m   with `install_apex`, base deps with `install_common_embodied_deps`. If a[m
[32m+[m[32m   utility *almost* fits, **enhance the utility**, don't fork a near-duplicate.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **A model has one `install_<model>_model()`** that `case`s on `$ENV_NAME` and[m
[32m+[m[32m   calls the matching `install_<env>_env()`. An env with **no** model is[m
[32m+[m[32m   installed through `install_env_only` (add a branch there).[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **System packages go in `requirements/embodied/sys_deps.sh`**, never[m
[32m+[m[32m   `apt-get`/`dnf`/`yum`/`pacman` inside `install.sh`. `sys_deps.sh` covers[m
[32m+[m[32m   apt/dnf/yum/pacman — add the package to **every** `install_deps_<mgr>`[m
[32m+[m[32m   function so all distros are handled.[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Pin every git dependency** to a commit/tag/branch (`@<rev>` or `-b[m
[32m+[m[32m   <branch>`), **or** fork it into `github.com/RLinf/<repo>`. No floating[m
[32m+[m[32m   `main`.[m
[32m+[m[32m5. **Don't touch RLinf's own `pyproject.toml` from `install.sh`** except through[m
[32m+[m[32m   `apply_torch_override`. If an override pin conflicts with a dependency you're[m
[32m+[m[32m   installing, `cd`/`pushd` into that dependency's checkout and install from[m
[32m+[m[32m   there (editing the *cloned* repo's pyproject after `cd` is fine).[m
[32m+[m[32m6. **Don't override core deps (`ray`, and avoid loose `torch` pins).** Before[m
[32m+[m[32m   adding a `uv pip install x==y`, check whether the common embodied/agentic[m
[32m+[m[32m   deps or `pyproject.toml` already provide it. Fewer overrides = fewer[m
[32m+[m[32m   cross-env breakages.[m
[32m+[m[32m7. **Every new model/env install needs a matching `docker/Dockerfile` change.**[m
[32m+[m[32m   Adding a model to `SUPPORTED_MODELS` or env to `SUPPORTED_ENVS` (and its[m
[32m+[m[32m   `install_*` function) is not complete until `docker/Dockerfile` has a build[m
[32m+[m[32m   stage that installs it. Add `base-image-embodied-<target>`, a `FROM[m
[32m+[m[32m   embodied-common-image AS embodied-<target>-image` stage, the `RUN bash[m
[32m+[m[32m   requirements/install.sh … --model <m> --env <e>` line, and the default-venv[m
[32m+[m[32m   `.bashrc` line. (See [add-install-docker-ci-e2e](../add-install-docker-ci-e2e/SKILL.md)[m
[32m+[m[32m   for the full stage + CI pattern.)[m
[32m+[m[32m8. **Keep it clean and simple.** Prefer a small `case` branch that calls shared[m
[32m+[m[32m   helpers over a long bespoke block of `sed`/`uv pip` hacks.[m
[32m+[m[32m9. **When uncertain, ask.** If you can't tell whether an override is required,[m
[32m+[m[32m   whether to fork-vs-pin, or whether a target genuinely needs a Docker image —[m
[32m+[m[32m   surface the question instead of guessing.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Common utilities to reuse (in `install.sh`)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Need | Use | Don't |[m
[32m+[m[32m|---|---|---|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Clone a repo | `clone_or_reuse_repo ENV_VAR DEFAULT_DIR URL [git args…]` (reuse via `*_PATH`, mirror prefix, corruption re-clone) | raw `git clone` |[m
[32m+[m[32m| flash-attn | `install_flash_attn` (platform-aware, prebuilt wheels, source fallback) | hand-built wheel URLs |[m
[32m+[m[32m| apex | `install_apex` | building apex inline |[m
[32m+[m[32m| venv + base sync | `create_and_sync_venv` then `install_common_embodied_deps` | re-implementing `uv venv` / `uv sync` |[m
[32m+[m[32m| torch version change | `--torch` flag → `apply_torch_override` | `sed` on `pyproject.toml` |[m
[32m+[m[32m| system libs / EGL / Vulkan | `requirements/embodied/sys_deps.sh` (+ per-platform render config) | `apt-get`, writing ICD json inline |[m
[32m+[m[32m| CUDA / ROCm detection | `detect_cuda_major_minor`, `detect_rocm_version` | re-parsing `nvcc`/`rocminfo` |[m
[32m+[m[32m| mirror-aware git | `GITHUB_PREFIX` prefix + `setup_mirror` | hardcoding mirror URLs |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Workflow[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Adding an env to a model:** add a branch to the model's `case "$ENV_NAME"`:[m
[32m+[m[32m`create_and_sync_venv` → `install_common_embodied_deps` → `install_<env>_env`[m
[32m+[m[32m(+ `install_flash_attn` if the model needs it). Register the env name in[m
[32m+[m[32m`SUPPORTED_ENVS`. **Then add the Dockerfile stage (Req 7).**[m
