[32m+[m[32m# Refine RLinf Docs[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBring a documentation page (or a whole section) up to the RLinf documentation[m
[32m+[m[32m**style guide**. Use this when writing a new page, rewriting an existing one, or[m
[32m+[m[32mdoing a style/structure pass.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe single source of truth is **`docs/STYLE_GUIDE.md`** — read it first and apply[m
[32m+[m[32mit. This skill is the operating procedure; the style guide holds the exact rules.[m
[32m+[m[32mWhen the two disagree, the style guide wins.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## When to use[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Editing/improving an existing page, or drafting a new one.[m
[32m+[m[32m- A "make this page match our docs style" / "clean up these docs" request.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Pair with the **docs-check** skill: `refine-docs` covers voice, structure, and[m
[32m+[m[32m  style; `docs-check` covers facts, code references, and EN/ZH parity.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Workflow[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Read `docs/STYLE_GUIDE.md`.** It is authoritative.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Find both language files.** Every page exists at `docs/source-en/...` and[m
[32m+[m[32m   `docs/source-zh/...`. Refine **both in the same pass** and keep them in parity.[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Classify the page**, then apply the matching part of the guide:[m
[32m+[m[32m   - **Landing / section / sub-section index** → cards or tables + a `:hidden:`[m
[32m+[m[32m     toctree; one-line outcome; routed list. Never body bullet lists.[m
[32m+[m[32m   - **Recipe / example page** (env, model, algorithm, SFT, robot) → the page[m
[32m+[m[32m     anatomy: figure + intro → `Overview` (4 aligned cards) → `Tasks` +[m
[32m+[m[32m     `Observation and Action` tables → `Installation` → `Download the Model` →[m
[32m+[m[32m     `Run It` → `Visualization and Results`. Use the standard section names and[m
[32m+[m[32m     the aligned card schema for that gallery subsection.[m
[32m+[m[32m   - **Concept / guide / reference / extending prose page** → outcome-first intro,[m
[32m+[m[32m     short sections, link out instead of inlining reference material.[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Apply the voice rules** to every paragraph: second person, imperative,[m
