[36m@@ -0,0 +1,180 @@[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m[32mname: test-install[m
[32m+[m[32mdescription: Test that requirements/install.sh works for an embodied model/env by building its venv and running the matching CI e2e test. Use when asked to test or verify an install, check a new model/env installs cleanly, run the e2e test for a model/env, confirm a venv works, or check that the model/checkpoint paths referenced by an e2e config actually exist on disk.[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mVerify that `requirements/install.sh` actually works for an embodied model/env:[m
[32m+[m[32mbuild its venv, confirm the e2e config's model paths exist, then run the matching[m
[32m+[m[32mCI e2e test against that venv. The harness is[m
[32m+[m[32m[.claude/skills/test-install/driver.py](.claude/skills/test-install/driver.py) —[m
[32m+[m[32mit reads the install command, env vars, and test config **straight out of**[m
[32m+[m[32m[.github/workflows/embodied-e2e-tests.yml](.github/workflows/embodied-e2e-tests.yml),[m
[32m+[m[32mso it never drifts from CI. Drive everything through that script.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAll paths below are relative to the repo root (the dir with `requirements/install.sh`).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Prerequisites[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis runs on the **embodied CI runner** (or an equivalent box): NVIDIA GPUs, the[m
[32m+[m[32mshared `/workspace/dataset/` tree (models, LIBERO, etc.), `uv`, and a `python3`[m
[32m+[m[32mthat has PyYAML. No `apt-get` needed — the driver only orchestrates. Quick check:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mnvidia-smi -L | head -1[m
[32m+[m[32mls -d /workspace/dataset >/dev/null && python3 -c "import yaml" && echo "env OK"[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf `python3` lacks PyYAML, the driver auto-reexecs under `uv run --with pyyaml`,[m
[32m+[m[32mso it works regardless.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Run (agent path)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe driver has seven subcommands. **Start with the read-only ones** (`list`,[m
[32m+[m[32m`resolve`, `check-paths`) — they're instant and tell you exactly what CI does[m
[32m+[m[32mbefore you spend an hour on an install.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32m# What model/env combos does CI cover, and which configs do they run?[m
[32m+[m[32mpython3 .claude/skills/test-install/driver.py list[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Show the exact install command + env vars + test configs for one combo:[m
[32m+[m[32mpython3 .claude/skills/test-install/driver.py resolve gr00t_n1d6 maniskill_libero[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Do the model/checkpoint paths an e2e config needs actually exist on disk?[m
[32m+[m[32mpython3 .claude/skills/test-install/driver.py check-paths libero_spatial_ppo_gr00t_n1d6[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Same check across every e2e config at once (great pre-flight / PR check):[m
[32m+[m[32mpython3 .claude/skills/test-install/driver.py check-all[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m`check-paths` classifies every absolute path in the config: `[model/input]`[m
[32m+[m[32m(must exist — a missing one fails the run before training and returns exit 1),[m
[32m+[m[32m`[output dir]` (created by the run, may be missing), `[path]` (informational).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### The full pipeline[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m`run` does install → check-paths (per config) → test, stopping a test whose[m
[32m+[m[32mrequired model paths are missing. **Always preview with `--dry-run` first** — it[m
[32m+[m[32mprints the exact shell (install line + CI test step) without executing:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mpython3 .claude/skills/test-install/driver.py run gr00t_n1d6 maniskill_libero \[m
[32m+[m[32m    --venv /workspace/test-venvs/gr00t_n1d6 --dry-run[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDrop `--dry-run` to actually build and test. Or drive the two halves separately[m
[32m+[m[32m(faster iteration — install once, test many):[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32m# Preview the install (env vars + install.sh line, with --venv and --use-mirror[m
[32m+[m[32m# injected). Drop --dry-run to build the venv; add --no-mirror to skip mirrors:[m
[32m+[m[32mpython3 .claude/skills/test-install/driver.py install gr00t_n1d6 maniskill_libero \[m
[32m+[m[32m    --venv /workspace/test-venvs/gr00t_n1d6 --dry-run[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Run the matching e2e test against any venv (verbatim CI test step, venv path[m
[32m+[m[32m# swapped in). This one is cheap — dummy SAC, 2 epochs — so run it for real:[m
[32m+[m[32mpython3 .claude/skills/test-install/driver.py test realworld_dummy_sac_cnn \[m
[32m+[m[32m    --venv /opt/venv/openvla[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mA full model install (e.g. `gr00t_n1d6`) is heavy — it clones repos and builds[m
[32m+[m[32mflash-attn — so preview with `--dry-run`, then run it where you can afford the[m
[32m+[m[32mtime. The dummy-SAC `test` above completes in a few minutes against the prebuilt[m
[32m+[m[32m`/opt/venv/openvla`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mA real test run spins up Ray, the env/rollout/policy workers, and trains for the[m
[32m+[m[32mconfig's (deliberately tiny) epoch count. The dummy-SAC smoke above finishes in a[m
[32m+[m[32mfew minutes and writes TensorBoard output under the config's `log_path`[m
[32m+[m[32m(`/workspace/results/<config>/tensorboard/`) — that directory appearing with[m
[32m+[m[32mfresh files is your "it worked" signal.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Clean up the venv when you're done[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mA test venv is heavy (e.g. `gr00t_n1d6` is ~600M) and is throwaway — it exists[m
[32m+[m[32monly to prove the install + e2e work. **After the test finishes, `rm -rf` the[m
[32m+[m[32m`--venv` path you built** unless the user asked to keep it for reuse:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mrm -rf /workspace/test-venvs/<model>[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDon't touch the shared caches (`/workspace/dataset/.uv`, `.uv_cache`) or the[m
[32m+[m[32mprebuilt `/opt/venv/*` — only the per-test venv you created. Cleaning up keeps[m
[32m+[m[32m`/workspace/test-venvs/` from accumulating stale multi-hundred-MB trees across[m
[32m+[m[32mruns. (Cleanup is for the venv only; the `/workspace/results/<config>/` outputs[m
[32m+[m[32mare your proof the test ran — leave them or mention them.)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### When there's no matching test[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf a model/env has an install but **no** e2e job in the workflow, `run` installs[m
[32m+[m[32mand then tells you there's nothing to run — **ask the user what to run** rather[m
[32m+[m[32mthan guessing. If you have a config name that isn't wired into CI, `test[m
[32m+[m[32m<config> --runner run|run_async|run_offline` runs it directly (pick the runner;[m
[32m+[m[32m`run` is the default).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Verifying a brand-new model/env (the common case)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhen someone adds `install_<model>_model()` + an e2e job (see the[m
[32m+[m[32m`add-install-docker-ci-e2e` and `install-check` skills), confirm it end to end:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32m# 1. CI parsed it correctly and the install command looks right:[m
[32m+[m[32mpython3 .claude/skills/test-install/driver.py resolve <model> <env>[m
[32m+[m[32m# 2. The SFT checkpoint the e2e config points at is actually on this box:[m
[32m+[m[32mpython3 .claude/skills/test-install/driver.py check-paths <its_config>[m
[32m+[m[32m# 3. Full build + test (preview with --dry-run, then drop it to run for real):[m
[32m+[m[32mpython3 .claude/skills/test-install/driver.py run <model> <env> \[m
[32m+[m[32m    --venv /workspace/test-venvs/<model> --dry-run[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf step 2 reports `MISS [model/input]`, the install can be perfect and the e2e[m
[32m+[m[32mwill still fail — the dataset/checkpoint just isn't staged on this runner. Surface[m
[32m+[m[32mthat to the user; it's not an install bug.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Gotchas[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **`install`/`run` need `--venv <path>`** — it's injected as `install.sh --venv`.[m
[32m+[m[32m  Use an absolute path (e.g. `/workspace/test-venvs/<model>`); a bare name lands[m
[32m+[m[32m  relative to the repo root. The `test` step then sources `<path>/bin/activate`.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **`--venv` reuses an existing venv** if one is already at that path (install.sh[m
[32m+[m[32m  validates the Python version and reuses it). For a truly clean install, point at[m
[32m+[m[32m  a fresh path or `rm -rf` it first.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **The driver runs CI's shell verbatim**, including its `export UV_PATH=/workspace/dataset/.uv`[m
[32m+[m[32m  etc. That's intentional — it reproduces CI exactly. It also means the install[m
[32m+[m[32m  writes into the shared uv cache, same as CI.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **`--use-mirror` is added to every install by default** (faster downloads),[m
[32m+[m[32m  even for CI jobs that don't list it. Pass `--no-mirror` to `install`/`run` to[m
[32m+[m[32m  turn it off. It's never duplicated if the CI job already has it.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Some jobs use `--platform amd`/`ascend`** (ROCm/Ascend runners) — `resolve`[m
[32m+[m[32m  shows the platform; those won't install on an NVIDIA box.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Some jobs do extra setup inside the test step** (e.g. `cp .../maniskill_assets/assets`[m
[32m+[m[32m  into the repo, or `export ROBOT_PLATFORM=ALOHA`). The driver replays the whole[m
[32m+[m[32m  CI test step, so those are included automatically — but they assume the asset[m
[32m+[m[32m  dirs exist under `/workspace/dataset/`.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **A duplicated config in `list`** (e.g. `d4rl_iql_mujoco,d4rl_iql_mujoco`) just[m
[32m+[m[32m  means the job runs that config twice with different flags (FSDP on/off). Normal.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Troubleshooting[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **`No CI job for model=… env=…`** — that combo isn't in the workflow. Run[m
[32m+[m[32m  `list` to see valid pairs; the model/env strings must match `--model`/`--env`[m
[32m+[m[32m  in `install.sh` exactly (`maniskill_libero`, not `libero`).[m
[32m+[m[32m- **`AttributeError: 'MessageFactory' object has no attribute 'GetPrototype'`** in[m
[32m+[m[32m  a test run — benign protobuf/TF-on-import noise from the workers, not a failure.[m
[32m+[m[32m  Look for the Ray `Placement(...)` lines and the rollout progress bar to confirm[m
[32m+[m[32m  real progress.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **`error: run this from inside the RLinf repo`** — `cd` to the repo root (the[m
[32m+[m[32m  dir containing `requirements/install.sh`) before invoking the driver.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Test exits 0 immediately but nothing trained** — you backgrounded it with `&`;[m
